OL,3,CSynthetic opioid deaths almost
OL,4,Cquadruple in England and Wales
OL,6,FDeaths linked to powerful synthetic
OL,7,Fopioids have almost quadrupled in
OL,8,FEngland and Wales in a year, while
OL,9,Foverall drug-related fatalities have
OL,10,Freached a record high, official
OL,11,Ffigures show.
OL,13,FData from the Office for National
OL,14,FStatistics (ONS) reveals that
OL,15,Ffatalities involving nitazenes, a
OL,16,Fpowerful class of synthetic opioids,
OL,17,Frose from 52 in 2023 to 195 in 2024.
OL,19,FThe National Crime Agency has linked
OL,20,Fnitazenes to 278 deaths across the UK.
